1.title: Cop Killer
1.plot: Ex-Los Angeles policeman, Christopher Dorner, declares war against law enforcement officers in California and goes on a cop killing spree. After an extensive manhunt Dorner is cornered near a ski resort in which Dorner refuses to surrender.

2.title: Passenger Plane Down
2.plot: In March 2015, young co-pilot Andreas Lubitz crashes a German airliner into the remote French Alps and kills all 150 passengers aboard the flight. The flight's data recorder shows that Lubitz crashes the plane intentionally.

3.title: Protected by Affluence
3.plot: Texas teen Ethan Couch kills four people while drinking and driving in Ft. Worth Texas. The 16-year-old is sentenced only to probation. His attorneys argue that his affluent life is the cause of his reckless actions.

4.title: Murder on the Lacrosse Team
4.plot: University of Virginia lacrosse player George Huguely goes on a binge that leads to a deadly encounter with his ex-girlfriend. His attorneys claim that her death is an accident - but a 63-minute police interrogation tape proves otherwise.

5.title: Bomb in Madrid
5.plot: In Madrid, Spain, 191 people are killed and more than 1,800 injured in a mass murder that becomes the deadliest Islamic attack in Western Europe to date.

6.title: Long Island Railroad Killer
6.plot: Collin Ferguson walks onto a Long Island Rail Road train in Queens and fires methodically at passengers over several minutes before he's disarmed and disabled by passengers.

7.title: Assassination of Anna
7.plot: Russian journalist, Anna Politkovskaya is a world-renowned writer and human rights activist. On Vladimir Putin's birthday, Politkovskaya is shot dead in the elevator of her apartment block in central Moscow.

8.title: Bomb in a Bali Nightclub
8.plot: On a warm October night, three bomb blasts tear through the tourist district of Kuta on the peaceful island of Bali. The attack kills 202 people and seriously injures 209 more.

9.title: Ice Pick Killer
9.plot: Luca Rocco Magnotta has a pathological need for attention. When he fails to get famous by more traditional means he turns to the internet to make a name for himself.

10.title: San Fransisco Dog Attack
10.plot: Diana Whipple is a beloved lacrosse coach whose life ends suddenly when she is brutally mauled to death just outside her San Francisco apartment.

11.title: Honeymoon Carjack
11.plot: Wealthy young newlyweds take a honeymoon to South Africa. But within days of their arrival the trip goes horribly wrong. Their taxicab is high jacked and the honeymoon ends in murder.

12.title: Revolutionaries and the Rich Girl
12.plot: When Patty Hearst, the daughter of a well-known media mogul is taken hostage by the SLA, America will be introduced to a bizarre psychological phenomenon known as 'Stockholm Syndrome'.

13.title: Self Defense or Murder
13.plot: A Minnesota man kills two teenagers after they break into his home. He claims he was defending his property and feared for his life. Chilling audio captures the sounds of Smith shooting the intruders.

14.title: Ohio Craigslist Killer
14.plot: 4 Men looking for work on the internet wind up on the business end of a gun. Who are these faceless killers luring victims to their death on social media?

15.title: On the Hunt for Humans
15.plot: A killer turns Phoenix Arizona into an urban hunting ground. As the bodies pile up both humans and animals turn up dead.

16.title: Oklahoma City Bombing
16.plot: A dark day in American history - the bombing of an Oklahoma City building by the now infamous Timothy McVeigh. Follow the FBI as they dig into the dark history of the man who killed 168 people in minutes.

17.title: Railway Killer
17.plot: A serial killer rides the rails across the United States, leaving a string of bloody murders behind him. But when two Florida teens go missing, can police find them before they cross paths with this dangerous killer?

18.title: Murder of the Mounties
18.plot: A mysterious shooter goes on a bloody rampage targeting police officers. As the shooting rages on, local residents update the nation in real time via social media.

19.title: Drugging Your Dates
19.plot: When Lucie Blackman goes missing in Japan the evidence leads back to wealthy businessman with an obsession for drugging and raping western women. His downfall is that he saves videos of his attacks.

20.title: British Pub Massacre
20.plot: An up and coming actor is stabbed to death while defending his brother in a street fight. As the investigation unfolds we discover that when a rowdy teen goes looking for a fight, he will usually find one.

21.title: Death by Dominatrix
21.plot: When a brilliant banker is found dead wearing only a head to toe bodysuit authorities spare no expense to find his killer. Did the sexy games go too far or is it murder?

22.title: Murder of a Finance Minister
22.plot: When two gunmen execute a Russian banker police wonder if he was involved with the Russian mafia. It turns out he was leading the charge to clean up corruption in the Russian banking system.

23.title: Dallas Cop Killer
23.plot: Army private Micah Xavier Johnson faces allegations of sexual harassment while deployed on a tour of duty in Afghanistan. The fallout from the charges turn him into a deadly assassin bent on shooting police.

24.title: Power Plant Shooter
24.plot: On a cold winters day in Ohio, after working for 30 years at the same factory, Timothy Hendron snaps and goes on a shooting rampage.

25.title: Baton Rouge Massacre
25.plot: Gavin Eugene Long takes the city of Baton Rouge by surprise with a brutal outburst of violence, panic and death targeting policeman in the line of duty.

26.title: Suffolk Strangler
26.plot: British fork-lift driver Steve Wright turns the sleepy county of Suffolk England into the scene of his sensational serial killing spree with the murder of five women working as prostitutes.

27.title: Speed Freak Killers
27.plot: Two childhood friends from San Joaquin, California grow into crazed and violent killers. Wesley Shermantine and Loren Herzog, fueled by week-long binges on speed, turn to murder.

28.title: Mysogynist Murderer
28.plot: In a small Australian town residents start finding bodies of dead women in rural locations. The bodies have strange marks and the investigation leads to a 20-year-old man named Paul Denyer.

29.title: Southside Slayer
29.plot: Los Angeles was a dangerous city in 1986 with over a 1,000 homicides reported with many going unsolved. The bodies of more than 50 African American women are dumped into the trash.

30.title: South African Strangler
30.plot: When a police reservist stumbles across a mass grave just outside of Johannesburg, South Africa. The investigation leads to the leader of a child advocacy group.

31.title: Camden Ripper
31.plot: An intense investigation is launched after a homeless man finds body parts in a dumpster. As more bags and bodies are discovered police canvas the neighborhood looking for leads.

32.title: Cosa Nostra Killer
32.plot: The life of Maurizio Avola is a cautionary tale about the mafia. He is drawn in at a young age by the power and respect it provides, however after decades as a hit man he is betrayed because he "knows too much.

33.title: Dr. Death
33.plot: An English doctor who makes house calls sounds wonderful to his elderly female patients, but when the family of a deceased patient challenges the will the truth is exhumed.

34.title: Deadly Affairs
34.plot: When a distinguished Navy doctor and his wife are founded stabbed inside their San Diego home, police launch a hunt for a brutal killer. The attack leaves the doctor dead, and his wife clinging to life.

35.title: Psycho Shooter
35.plot: In 2011, a lone gunman sets off on a ruthless killing spree at an Arizona shopping center. His target, Congresswoman Gabrielle Giffords. After killing six and wounding thirteen, police capture a disturbed, twenty-two-year-old suspect.

36.title: Killers by Blood
36.plot: When a beloved grandfather goes missing in rural Utah, investigators begin a multi-state search for him. What starts as a simple missing persons case becomes a complex crime of kidnapping, betrayal and a shocking murder.

37.title: Texas Teen Love Triangle
37.plot: A beautiful high school girl goes missing in the middle of the night without a trace. When her body is found, the entire community of Mansfield, Texas is in shock.

38.title: Pickaxe Murders
38.plot: Houston, Texas is rocked by a grisly crime scene- a man whose head is practically hammered off his body and a semi-nude woman riddled with pickax wounds.

39.title: Fast Food Massacre
39.plot: A Wendy's restaurant in Queens, New York is hit by a pair of robbers just before closing time. The robbery escalates as the pair slaughter five employees, while leaving another two for dead.

40.title: Bound to Die
40.plot: Nineteen year-old Elizabeth "Lizzi" Marriott goes missing. The investigation leads to Kat McDonough who claims that Marriott died during rough sex. After accepting a plea deal, she admitted that she offered Marriott up for sex.

41.title: Texas Tower Sniper
41.plot: In America's first mass slaying, a sniper randomly guns down students and pedestrians from atop the University of Texas clock tower. Police have no plan in place for such an event; the police are out-gunned and over their heads.

42.title: Co-Ed Killer
42.plot: Young, female students have disappeared with alarming frequency from the college town of Santa Cruz, California. Then mutilated body parts show up as almost a human jigsaw puzzle.

43.title: Hawaiian Horror
43.plot: When a killer burst into a Honolulu conference room at a button-down, no nonsense office, he leaves behind seven dead - and the biggest mass slaying in Hawaiian history.

44.title: The Killer Nurse
44.plot: At hospitals in New Jersey and Pennsylvania, patients are mysteriously dying. After the Reverend Gall unexpectedly dies in 2003, tests reveal that he has five times the dose of medication that he was prescribed.

45.title: Snuff Film Killers
45.plot: On May 14, 2006, a fisherman in Bates City, Missouri, discovers the nude body of a woman ,41-year-old Marsha Spicer.

46.title: Christmas Eve Massacre
46.plot: A man wearing a Santa suit makes a surprise visit to a Pardo family Christmas Eve party in Covina, California, in 2008. The man is carrying a gift-wrapped flamethrower in one hand and in the other, a handgun.

47.title: Fiendish Friend
47.plot: Samuel Herr and Julie Kibuishi are a young couple living in Orange County, California. On May 22, 2010, Julie's partially clothed body is discovered in Herr's apartment, and Herr, apparently, is on the run.

48.title: The Makeover Murder
48.plot: Former beauty queen Michele MacNeill, married to prominent surgeon Martin MacNeill, raises their eight children. At her husband's urging, she gets a face lift. On April 11, 2011, her husband finds her dead in the bathtub.

49.title: Bus Stop Killer
49.plot: Columbus, Ohio's Jessica Keen, cheerleader and honor student, gets in a heated argument with her boyfriend, and they break up. Jessica strolls to a nearby bus stop. This is the last time anyone sees her alive.

50.title: House of Horrors
50.plot: In Gloucester, England, Rosemary Letts meets 27-year old Frederick West, married father of two daughters, on her 15th birthday. They move in together, and soon, one of his daughters, and then his wife, disappear.

51.title: The Contemptuous Killer
51.plot: A man abducts 16-year old Colette Aram in Nottinghamshire, England and strangles her. Twenty-five years pass until a DNA sample matches the blood at the crime scene. It turns out the killer is related.

52.title: Dangerous Obsession
52.plot: Joanna Clare Yeates is a 25-year old landscape architect from Hampshire, England, who goes missing. Eight days later, someone finds her strangled body along the roadside.

53.title: Mexican Wrestling Maniac
53.plot: Someone is strangling elderly women throughout Mexico City. There's no apparent connection among the victims, and no apparent motive. After a police investigation goes nowhere, the killer is caught red-handed.

54.title: Panic at Canyon Lake
54.plot: The upscale, gated-community of Canyon Lake, California seems like the safest place on earth. Yet, someone is mysteriously murdering old ladies. Detectives uncover a trail of credit card fraud that leads them to a surprise killer.

55.title: Evil Stranger
55.plot: When a young woman disappears from the streets of Southampton, England, police launch a massive manhunt. But the killer is one step ahead and flees to India. The victim's parents pursue this killer to get justice for their daughter.

56.title: Deadly Curves
56.plot: Florida is the land of beaches, nightclubs, and big booty's. Some seeking a curvaceous physique visit one self-proclaimed doctor injects tire-sealant, bathtub caulk, and liquid cement into her patients- with homicidal consequences.

57.title: Stranger at the Station
57.plot: When a popular young student mysteriously goes missing her boyfriend tells police the last time he sees her is at Oxford station with a mysterious stranger at her side. The police sketch bears a resemblance to someone close to her.

58.title: Machette Murders
58.plot: In 1971, someone hacks to death twenty-five men and buries them in shallow graves in a California orchard. The following investigation shocks the nation, sparks charges of racial bias, and introduces America to a new term: serial killer.

59.title: Vulture Feeder Fiend
59.plot: During their investigation into serial killer Ed Kemper police zero in on the killer, they discover a follower of the occult who believes he is sacrificing people to save humanity.

60.title: Knight of Swords
60.plot: In Santa Cruz, California, police believe they have another Manson family-type serial killer on their hands when they come across a series of ritualistic killings.

61.title: Dixie Mafia
61.plot: Legendary lawman Buford Pusser cuts his teeth battling the Dixie Mafia, a rogue's gallery of thieves, crooked gamblers, and killers operating in the American South.

62.title: Gambled on Murder
62.plot: In London, prim and proper Carole Waugh is leading a double life. Through her tawdry escort work, she meets a gambler and a swindler. The con goes on after Carol suddenly goes missing.

63.title: Semper Free
63.plot: Yvonne Baldelli and Marine Corps veteran Brian Brimager fall in love and move to a Caribbean island. But paradise turns into a nightmare when Yvonne e-mails that she's left Brian for another man and they're moving to Costa Rica.

64.title: Kiss of Death
64.plot: The most vulnerable patients in an Ohio hospital are dying at an alarming rate. Someone close to these patients decides who lives and who dies after receiving signs from a demonic spirit guide.

65.title: Ashes to Ashes
65.plot: When a trashcan is found holding the decomposed body of a woman, an international investigation follows to find her killer. Police suspect a top chef of cooking up a recipe for disaster.

66.title: Collar Bomb Killer
66.plot: A pizza deliveryman enters a bank wearing a bomb around his neck, claiming he's being forced to rob the bank. After the bomb goes off, investigators look into one of the strangest robberies ever.

67.title: Day of Retribution
67.plot: There's a killing spree in Santa Barbara. When the dust settles, it appears the killer snaps when he doesn't win the $120-million lottery, dashing his plans to get a girlfriend and lose his virginity.

68.title: Double Crossed
68.plot: On a lonely California highway, a prominent doctor and his wife are shot point blank in their car. An investigation reveals that the doctor gets a referral from his mistress for a hit man to kill his wife. What could possibly go wrong.

69.title: Folsom Wolves
69.plot: A series of random killings in Redlands, California leaves police with no clues. But then the manager of a fast food restaurant finds the ID of one victim in the trash. And with it, another ID which leads to a suspect.

70.title: Episode #2.70
70.plot: A series of random killings in Redlands, California leaves police with no clues. But then the manager of a fast food restaurant finds the ID of one victim in the trash. And with it, another ID which leads to a suspect.

71.title: The Christmas That Wasn't
71.plot: It will test the skill of investigators to solve the Christmas Eve killings of a couple murdered 27-years ago. A jailhouse informant and tenacious police work make sure one killer receives 103 years in prison.

72.title: Cabin Fervor
72.plot: Stephen Epperly takes Gena Hall to a cabin in the woods of Virginia to an intimate late night party. But when the other couple arrives, Epperly shouts out that they're leaving. No one ever sees Gina again.

73.title: Sinister Minister
73.plot: When a parishioner commits suicide in his pastor's officer, it opens up a Pandora's Box of adultery, deceit, and murder. Does a well-respected man of God find a simple way out of his vows, "till death do us part"?

74.title: S&M and Murder
74.plot: A sex slave in Norfolk, England, says she will do anything it takes to prove her obedience to a sadistic, psychopathic master. When he tests her by handing over a list of people for her to murder, will she comply?

75.title: Evil Eyes
75.plot: One morning in 1990, someone in a Dallas, Texas suburb finds the body of a prostitute, her eyes surgically removed. Two similar murders later, the FBI zeroes in on a killer whose obsession is taxidermy.

1.title: Murder in Michigan
1.plot: A marriage, plagued by resentment and affairs, hits it's tipping point and ends in a gruesome murder. Plus, a surgically precise and digitally orchestrated heist known as Unlimited Operation drains banks of nearly $45 Million globally.

2.title: Primary Suspect
2.plot: Joran Van Der Sloot, the primary suspect in the unsolved murder of American woman Natalee Holloway is convicted of murdering a Peruvian woman. Plus, an angry soccer player fatally assaults a referee over a penalty call.

3.title: One-Eyed Butcher
3.plot: Dale Cregan, one-eyed drug dealer and cold-blooded murderer whose calling card is a grenade. Plus, one of the top New York mob families' steal more than 5 million dollars worth of cash and jewels from the Lufthansa airlines vault.

4.title: Fiancee Tried for Homicide
4.plot: A man is found dead. Ten years later his fiancée is convicted for the murder, but the verdict is overturned. Why? Plus, football brought him fame; conspiring to murder the woman carrying his unborn child brought him infamy.

5.title: Murder at 13,000 Feet
5.plot: A murder at 13,000 feet. A classic who dunnit love triangle between a schoolteacher, a married mother of two and a hot skydiving instructor. Plus, Wolfgang Beltracchi's paintings are world famous- but one problem - turns out they are fakes.

6.title: The Hiccup Murder
6.plot: A shy teen makes headlines for 5 weeks of non-stop hiccups. Four years later, she makes headlines again, for murder. Plus, a behind the scenes look at the downfall of "Fixer" to Hollywood's elite, Anthony Pellicano.

7.title: Killer Cross-Dresser
7.plot: A middle-aged Denver couple hires a homeless housekeeper. He shows his thanks by bludgeoning the couple to death. Plus, in a jealous rage, an American Astronaut, goes on a 900-mile road trip to seek retribution from her ex-lover's new lady.

8.title: Reality Kills
8.plot: Former "Survivor" producer Bruce Beresford-Redmond kills his wife during a family vacation. Plus, a small southern California city nearly goes bankrupt as the victim of a citywide corruption scandal.

9.title: The Mountie Murderer
9.plot: One morning a troubled Royal Canadian Mountie Officer hits the tipping point and snaps killing one of his own. Plus, the son of a Las Vegas judge robs 1.5 million from the Bellagio Casino, dressed in full biker gear.

10.title: A Deadly Druglord
10.plot: Vicente Fuentes rules his cartel with a bloody grip, responsible for mass murders and billions in drug trafficking. Plus, one of the most popular and longest serving U.S. mayors is accused of running a corrupt criminal enterprise.

11.title: Murder in the Basement
11.plot: Up and coming actress Alexandra Ducsay is murdered in her own home. For years this cold case goes unsolved until a key piece of evidence resurfaces years later.

12.title: The Master of Revenge Porn
12.plot: A website posts explicit photos of people, without their permission, and demands payment to remove them. This extortion is called "Revenge Porn". Plus, "El Chapo" runs one of the world's largest drug trafficking organizations in the world.

13.title: Killer Imposter
13.plot: A German impostor and killer on the run- Christian Gerhartreiter - masquerades across the US under a guise - as an heir to the fabled Rockefeller fortune. He thinks getting away with murder is his final con, but he's wrong.

14.title: An American Spy
14.plot: FBI agent Robert Hanssen's treachery has been called the worst breach of U.S. intelligence in the history of the FBI. Plus, WorldCom executives fix the company's accounting numbers for their own personal game.

15.title: Murder in the LAPD
15.plot: The Los Angeles Police Department's Rampart division is home to dozens of corrupt officers. The officers are committing heinous crimes, possibly even murder. One officer is at the center of it all and his arrest has a domino effect.

16.title: The Loony Loomis Fargo Heist
16.plot: In October 1997, an armored car driver for Loomis Fargo and Company leads a team in a brazen heist stealing $17.3 million from the Loomis vault.

17.title: The Crooked Mayor Affair
17.plot: The youngest Mayor of Detroit and biggest hope for the dying city, ends up single handedly destroying it. Plus, when a dark secret is revealed about the outspoken wife of Northern Ireland's First Minister the public is stunned.

18.title: Murder as Revenge
18.plot: A small town judge goes down a dark path of revenge and murder, leaving an entire town in fear. Plus, with the help of his internationally honored father, the world had high hopes for Jesse Jackson Jr. until his legacy crashed amid scandal.

19.title: The Handsome Killer
19.plot: The Preppy Murder made international headlines and exposed the excessive living of NY's upper crust kids. Plus, Melissa King is the benefits manager for the "Sandhogs" Union. Over the course of 7 years, she steals over $40 million dollars.

20.title: The Druglord of the Skies
20.plot: Pablo Escobar is the drug kingpin of the world. He is the most successful criminal the underworld has ever seen. Plus, a scam artist goes from aviation entrepreneur to managing and ripping off boy bands like Backstreet Boys and 'NSYNC.

21.title: The Negligent Director
21.plot: Reckless film director Randall Miller sets up a risky shot on a live railroad track resulting in disaster. Plus, George Trofimoff is the highest-ranking U.S. military officer ever convicted of spying.

22.title: The Notorious Lobbyist
22.plot: Jack Abramoff is one of the most successful US Lobbyists in history. However, his tactics aren't quite legal. Plus, the chairman of Daewoo is charged with masterminding accounting fraud worth 41 trillion dollars.

23.title: Celebrity Obsessed Crooks
23.plot: A group of celebrity-obsessed teens break into the homes of Hollywood Stars, steal millions and are proud of it.

24.title: The Hit King
24.plot: Baseball's all-time hits leader Pete Rose is banned from baseball for allegedly betting on games while he was a player and manager.

25.title: The Hedge Fund Fraudster
25.plot: A Sri Lankan billionaire is arrested for insider trading as part of the largest ever-SEC case against a hedge fund. Plus, "The Wolf of Wall Street" makes millions running a boiler room as part of penny stock scam.

26.title: A Rogue Trader
26.plot: A rogue broker whose unauthorized speculative trading causes the spectacular collapse of Barings Bank. Plus, Seven-time Tour de France winner Lance Armstrong is accused of doping and stripped of everything.

27.title: Murder at the Boston Marathon
27.plot: Dzhokhar Tsarnaev and his brother Tamerlan set two pressure cooker bombs at the finish line of the 2013 Boston Marathon. The explosion kills 3 and injures over 200 people.

28.title: The Unscrupulous Judge
28.plot: Two Pennsylvania judges abuse their power to unjustly throw thousands of kids into juvenile detention centers in exchange for millions in kickbacks.

29.title: The Dumb Crook
29.plot: Hours after robbing a bank in Waco, Nebraska, the 19 year-old culprit brags about it on YouTube along with her shocking reasons for doing it.

30.title: The Badboy Rockstar
30.plot: AC/DC drummer Phil Rudd lives the life of a bad boy rock star. But Rudd's temper leads to charges of threatening to kill and drug possession.

31.title: Terror Attack at 30,000 Feet
31.plot: Pan Am Flight 103, from London to New York blows up over Lockerbie, Scotland in a horrific attack. Plus, Lutfur Rahman is the first directly elected independent mayor of Tower Hamlets. However, multiple scandals plague his time in office.

32.title: The Sydney Cafe Massacre
32.plot: Man Haron Monis, takes a Sydney cafe and its patron's hostage for over two days in December 2014. Plus, 'Kid Cannabis' is a 19-year old pizza delivery boy by day and a multi-millionaire drug kingpin by night.

33.title: The Gangland Murders of Australia
33.plot: In the underworld of the Australia, drug trafficking explodes in an all-out war as retribution murders between nearly half a dozen crime syndicates.

34.title: The Good Wife Murder
34.plot: Jane Bashara is found strangled to death in her car, her husband of 26 years, Bob, has many secrets and lives a double life. When the truth comes out, it is shocking.

35.title: A Designer Death
35.plot: Rudolph Moshammer, one of Germany's most successful fashion designers, is found murdered at the hands of a male prostitute. Plus, Christian rock star, Tim Lambesis, spirals out of control and gets caught up in a murder for hire plot.

36.title: The Long Island Lolita
36.plot: Known as "The Long Island Lolita", teenager, Amy Fisher, shoots her 35 year old lover's wife in the head, in hopes of killing her, but she survives to tell the story.

37.title: The Largest Terror Plot Since 9-11
37.plot: A homegrown terrorism group plans a jihad through a series of bombings against the US in Southern California. Federal officials call it the most operational advanced plot since 9/11.

38.title: Britain's Most Notorious Inmate
38.plot: He is called the most violent prisoner in Britain. While incarcerated, he's attacked over 20 prison guards and countless prisoners, and taken 11 hostages. Plus, it's the largest online manhunt in history.

39.title: Death on the High Seas
39.plot: A 7 day cruise on the Costa Concordia ends in disaster when a reckless captain orders his ship off-course, causing it to hit a boulder and sink. Chaos ensues and many lives are lost.

40.title: A Murder in Italy
40.plot: When a young-American college student spends a semester studying abroad, she finds herself facing a lifetime behind bars when her roommate is murdered.

41.title: Anchorwoman Murder
41.plot: Popular television news anchor and rising star, Anne Pressly, is brutally murdered in her Little Rock Arkansas home. Plus, Kevin Trudeau, a radio and TV personality and successful author is accused of fraud and larceny.

42.title: Murder by Teacup
42.plot: When Russian federal agents poison exiled spy, Alexander Litvinenko, everyone wonders if the Kremlin is behind the attack.

43.title: A TV Icon Accused of Murder
43.plot: TV icon Robert Blake is accused of murdering his second wife, Bonnie Lee Bakley. A tense trial ends when he's found not guilty, but questions still remain.

44.title: Mass Murder in the Ukraine
44.plot: The "Beast of Ukraine" murders over 52 people because, he says, voices in his head make him kill. Plus, the most lucrative instance of insider trading occurs when a hotshot broker gets 'tips' on a promising experimental Alzheimer drug.

45.title: Murder of a Fashion Icon
45.plot: Andrew Cunanan is on the FBI's most wanted list after a killing spree that ends with the death of fashion icon, Gianni Versace.

46.title: The Starlet Murder
46.plot: A young actress lands her big break in Hollywood, but her dreams are cut short when an obsessed fan fatally shoots her. Plus, when New York's elite needs an escort they go to her. Meet "The Mayflower Madam."

47.title: A Death on Staten Island
47.plot: Eric Garner, a Staten Island father of six, is tragically killed when an NYPD officer puts Garner into what is described as an illegal chokehold. Plus, the FBI hunt down Kevin Mitnick, one of the most famous computer hackers of all time.

48.title: The War Criminal
48.plot: A high-ranking government official authorizes the arrests and subsequent deportations of over 1,400 Jews to Nazi concentration camps where most of them perish.

49.title: The Death Doctor
49.plot: A renowned cancer doctor intentionally misdiagnoses thousands of patients with cancer as part of a major insurance scam. Plus, Parmalat, a global power in the dairy industry, conspire in one of the biggest fraud cases in Italy's history.

50.title: The Stripper Stabbing
50.plot: Crystal Gail Mangum made headlines for falsely accuses the Duke University men's lacrosse team of rape. A few years later, she's charged with the attempted murder of her boyfriend.

51.title: The Music Producer Murder
51.plot: Critics call legendary music producer, Phil Spector, a genius, but the music can't save him from being convicted of murder. Plus, a "Virginia Jihad Network" of young U.S. Muslim men play paintball to train for holy war.

52.title: Bin Laden's Triple Threat
52.plot: He is the most dangerous triple-agent in US history. He duped the United States for more than a decade, serving in the US Military, FBI, and CIA, while simultaneously helping orchestrate the al Qaeda campaign of terror that led to 9/11.

53.title: The Minister Murder
53.plot: David Chenery-Wickens, a fortune-telling conman kills his wife while having affairs with his flock of female followers. At trial, the murderous preacher is exposed as a liar and Casanova.

54.title: The Hammer Homicide
54.plot: A battered woman beats her husband to death with a claw hammer while he sleeps. Plus, one of China's most powerful leaders is sentenced to life in prison for bribery, abuse of power, and leaking state secrets.

55.title: Jet Set Murder
55.plot: A British male model turned playboy has a very rough night of sex, drugs and violence, which ends in murder. Plus, a mother-daughter trip to paradise turns deadly with a body stuffed in a suitcase in Bali.

56.title: Murder by Capsule
56.plot: Stella Nickell is the first person tried and convicted of causing death by product tampering . The motive - her husband's insurance policy.

57.title: Celebrity Son Murder
57.plot: Ennis Cosby, the only son of Bill and Camille Cosby, is senselessly gunned down on the streets of LA while changing a tire.

58.title: Reckless Deaths on a Hollywood Set
58.plot: Vic Morrow is starring in the feature film "Twilight Zone: The Movie" when a stunt goes horribly wrong, causing three tragic deaths.

59.title: Terrorists Kill Soldier
59.plot: Two radical Muslims brutally murder a British solider in the middle of a busy London street, all caught on tape.

60.title: Movie Theater Massacre
60.plot: James Holmes is found guilty of murdering 12 people and injuring 70 more in a shooting rampage at a Colorado movie theater on July 20, 2012 that rocked the nation.

61.title: Polo King's Deadly Hit and Run
61.plot: Florida polo enthusiast and billionaire John Goodman blows through a stop sign and slams into another car, killing a college student. And a celebrity publicist backs her SUV into a crowd outside a nightclub, then flees the scene.

62.title: From Student Seduction to Murder
62.plot: High school staffer Pamela Smart become a household name when she starts a love affair with a student, who she convinces to kill her husband.

63.title: North Hollywood Gun Battle
63.plot: Los Angeles police respond to a bank heist and find they are outgunned by the robbers. Citizens and police run for cover in a brazen deadly shootout.

64.title: Dark Family Secrets Turn Deadly
64.plot: A son beats his mother to death in a savage attack. A family dark secrets come to light as police investigate a murder case against Jeffrey Pyne.

65.title: Attempt to Kill a President
65.plot: Obsessed stalker John Hinkley, Jr. will do anything to gain fame and the attention of a young Hollywood star, even if it means killing the President of the United States.

66.title: Black Widows
66.plot: Two elderly Los Angeles widows target homeless men in their deadly plots to cash in on murder. And charismatic art investor Kenneth Ira Starr bilks Hollywood celebrities out of millions of dollars.

67.title: Killer Conviction- Justice or Mistake?
67.plot: A young Idaho man confesses to a vicious murder. But did police steer Christopher Tapp to make a false confession and send the wrong man to prison? And white supremacist Buford Furrow goes on a killing spree in Los Angeles.

68.title: The Chessboard Killer
68.plot: A deranged man goes on a killing spree near Moscow. Alexander Pichushkin seeks to become Russia's most prolific serial killer. Plus, New York art dealer Larry Salander swindles his big-name clients.

69.title: Murder in the Lab
69.plot: Yale University doctoral student Annie Le vanishes while working in her lab. Days later, her body is found stuffed inside a basement wall. Also, Hollywood actor Wesley Snipes ends up in the cross-hairs of the IRS.

70.title: Five Marriages and Five Dead Husbands
70.plot: Something doesn't add up when years of broken marriages result in the deaths of five husbands. Police catch a killer wife. Also, a man obsessed with his faith goes on a deadly rampage.

71.title: Death of the King of Pop
71.plot: Minutes after pop star Michael Jackson dies, his personal physician launches a cover-up. As detectives investigate Jackson's death, they focus on Dr. Conrad Murray. Plus, the greedy stock trader who nearly took down Wall Street.

72.title: Tragedy in Waco
72.plot: Self-proclaimed Messiah David Koresh takes on federal agents in a bloody gun battle that kills ATF personnel and Koresh's followers. The death toll skyrockets when a 51-day standoff that ends in a fiery tragedy.

73.title: Death of a Football Legend
73.plot: A secret affair ends in tragedy for pro football legend Steve McNair. What led to the murder-suicide of a football hero and his mistress? Also, Chicago cop Jon Burge pushes cruel and unusual punishment to the extreme.

74.title: Murder in China
74.plot: As investigators look into the murder of a British businessman in China, all signs point to a prominent family in the Chinese Communist Party. Also, the Hollywood Madam who provides beautiful escorts for her A-list clients.

75.title: Milkshake Murder
75.plot: "Milkshake murderer"Nancy Kissel incapacitates her husband with a strawberry milkshake full of sedatives before bludgeoning him to death. Also, the U.S. goes after the leader of a Mexican drug cartel.

76.title: Deadly Religion
76.plot: Religious cult leader Jim Jones leads hundreds of followers in a mass suicide in the jungles of South America, after the assassination of a U.S. congressmen.

77.title: Cashing Out on Murder
77.plot: A wife claims her husband has run off with another woman. But years later, the missing husband is found dead, dismembered and stuffed in a box.

78.title: Deadly Satire
78.plot: Two terrorists out for blood go on a deadly rampage in Paris over editorial cartoons in the magazine Charlie Hebdo that target their satire at the prophet Muhammad.

79.title: Killer Attack at LAX
79.plot: Is it a hate crime or an act of terrorism when an Egyptian immigrant opens fire at the El Al ticket counter at Los Angeles International Airport? Also, three bank-robbing, gun-firing siblings elude police across 15 states.

80.title: From NFL Stardom to Murder
80.plot: Star tight end Aaron Hernandez goes from the football record books to life in prison when his off the field exploits end in murder.

81.title: Scarsdale Diet Murder
81.plot: Doctor and best-selling author Dr. Herman Tarnower is killed by his lover, the head mistress at a prestigious private school. Also, a series of vicious killings terrorize a southern community.

82.title: Murdered by Twin Daughters
82.plot: Teenaged twin sisters claim an intruder breaks into their home and kills their mother. But police uncover a crime that is far more sinister.

83.title: A Motown Family Tragedy
83.plot: Motown legend Marvin Gaye is shot and killed in a family tragedy that involves abuse, heated arguments and drugs. Also, when a prominent doctor's wife slips and falls in the shower, investigators see that it's not a fatal accident.

84.title: Singing Fame and Family Horror
84.plot: Jennifer Hudson soars to fame on the hit TV show American Idol. But life for the singer's family turns tragic. Also, authorities race to catch the person who tries to set off a bomb in Times Square.

85.title: License to Kill
85.plot: Wherever Doctor Michael Swango goes, sickness and death follow. Investigators try to stop a murderer who has a license to kill. Also, when a well-liked dental hygienist files for divorce, the wife and mother vanishes.

86.title: Targeting an American Terrorist
86.plot: American citizen Anwar Al-Awlaki is killed by a US drone strike after the once peaceful holy man joins the top ranks of Al Qaeda. Also, a vengeful accountant hopes to silence his wife.

87.title: Olympic Bomber
87.plot: Eric Rudolph sets off a bomb at the Atlanta Olympics, then launches deadly bombings at a southern abortion clinic and a gay bar. Police search the wilderness for years trying to find their killer.

88.title: Murder by Mercedes
88.plot: A prominent couple with a thriving dental practice ends up in a murderous love triangle when the family car turns into a deadly weapon. Also, a 911 call and a toy gun end in a tragic shooting at an Ohio Wal Mart.

89.title: Real Estate Tycoon's Murder
89.plot: When a car bomb kills an Arizona businessman outside a country club, investigators wonder if it's a mob hit, or an ex-wife out for cash. Also, a model's sexual con game turns into a deadly dinner.

90.title: Killer Sunday School Teachers
90.plot: An adulterous affair between two Sunday school teachers leads to a husband's murder. Also, a famous Bollywood stars claims he's innocent in the death of a homeless man.

91.title: Double Murder Affair
91.plot: When an affair heats up between a married man and a married woman, a husband and a wife are killed. But the murderous truth isn't discovered for nearly twenty years.

92.title: Runaway Bride
92.plot: Police launch a massive manhunt when a bridge-to-be disappears. Is it a crime or the wedding jitters? Also, a Mexican drug lord claims his cartel is a necessary evil that protects people from even bloodier rivals.

93.title: Angel of Death
93.plot: When patients start dying unexpectedly at California hospitals, investigators wonder if it's natural causes or the work of an Angel of Death. And a bride-to-be uses a string of lies to escape her impending marriage.

94.title: The Yorkshire Ripper
94.plot: A vicious killer is on the loose in Yorkshire, England. He preys on the most vulnerable people using household tools to commit murder. And when a husband is killed, is it a tragic accident or the murderous plot of his wife?

95.title: Deadly Couple
95.plot: Brother and sister Jerad and Amanda Miller take their extremist views on a violent and deadly rampage. Also, a husband is pushed over the edge when his teacher wife begins dating one of her former students.

96.title: Casanova Serial Killer
96.plot: A good-looking wanderer picks up women in country western bars, and after charming them, he kills them. Police launch a coast-to-coast manhunt for the Casanova killer.

97.title: Until Death Do Us Part
97.plot: A young Michigan wife and mom believes murder is easier than divorce in a chilling murder-for-hire. And US investigators accuse a suspected terrorist of plotting to detonate a 'dirty bomb'.

98.title: Troubled Teen or Brutal Killer
98.plot: She admits to abusing drugs and stripping for money, but young Nevada woman Kirsten Lobato says she is no killer. And in another case, a real-life soap opera turns into a twisted and lethal tale.

99.title: Killer Day Trader
99.plot: When Mark Barton's wife is murdered, the mild-mannered chemist uses the insurance money to dive into the risky world of day trading. Also, the sky's the limit for a hot designer who turns his young models into victims of sexual abuse.

100.title: Killer Arsonist
100.plot: A California arsonist ignites a fire that burns wildly out of control, and within hours, five firefighters are dead. And a Texas mom will do anything to win her daughter a spot on the high school cheer squad.

101.title: The Step-Father Murder
101.plot: A teenaged girl calls 911, claiming a masked intruder has just murdered her step-father. But police investigators believe someone is telling lies.

102.title: Murder in the House of Gucci
102.plot: A scorned ex-wife schemes to save a family fortune and her position of power by hiring a hit man to kill her ex-husband, Mauarizio Gucci. Also, when parents stand in the way of young love, a teenager hatches a shocking plan.

103.title: South African Treason
103.plot: The Boeremag, a right-wing organization in South Africa, attempts to overthrow the democratic majority rule by force. Also, classmates think a 15-year-old boy is just blowing off steam when he threatens to kill his parents.

104.title: Deadly Rampage at Fort Hood
104.plot: An Army psychiatrist goes on a shooting rampage at Fort Hood, Texas, in the worst mass shooting ever at a domestic US military base.

imdb.title: Corrupt Crimes
plot: _Corrupt Crimes_ (qv) investigates recent crime stories in complete detail, with expert analysis and dramatic storytelling. Cases include crimes of passion, espionage, treason, insider trading, government corruption, murder and conspiracies.
